    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-01-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-01-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="719"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d719">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Terrell</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-01-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 4, 1896</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 762.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your Nos. 705 and 709, of December 4 and 5,
                    respectively, in regard to the destruction of American property at Harpoot, have
                    been received. With the former you inclosed a statement of the American losses,
                    which foot up $87,985, and with the latter a letter from Rev. Mr. Barnum, which
                    circumstantially shows the connivance of the higher military officers at Harpoot
                    in the attack on the Christian quarter and their responsibility for the
                    unchecked destruction of the American buildings.</p>
                <p>The Department approves your announced intention to demand indemity for these
                    losses and those at Marash as soon as the amount of the latter is known.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
